        <li>FOSS Developers & Designers: Matt Hill (Start9), Skot9000 (BitAxe), Brett Rowan (PyASIC), 100AcresRanch (Thermohashostat)</li>
        <li>Mining Decentralization: Bitcoin Mechanic, Boerst</li>
        <li>Energy Experts: Upstream Data, Compass Mining, Saz Mining, Distributed Hash, Guardrail Mining</li>
        <li>Trades, HVAC, Plumbing, Electrical & Engineering: Long HVAC and Controls, Tessere, Insol Corp, Rox Heating, Colorado Air Filter</li>
        <li>Bitcoin Media and Education: Rob Warren (Bitcoin Miners Almanac), Trevor Bello (Build a Mine Podcast / Bitcoin Mining World), DJ Valerie B Love (Bitcoin for Peace)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  <!-- Travel Section -->
  <div class="mt-10">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Travel Information</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      The Space is located in an easily accessible part of Denver (3700 N Franklin St, Denver CO). Here are some recommendations for your stay:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-4">
      <li>If you're only coming to town for Undermine, you don't need a rental car. If you are planning a ski trip or other travels around the summit, have at it.</li>
      <li>The Denver RTD (Light Rail Transit) Train travels from the Denver Airport to Union Station every 15 minutes. A day pass ticket costs $10. Get off at the second to last stop, 38th and Blake St.</li>
      <li>The Space has 5 parking spots behind the building. First come, first serve. Please be aware some parking spots may be reserved for summit activities. There is plenty of street parking around the venue.</li>
      <li>There are three hotels within walking distance of The Space: Catbird, Vib, Cambria. There are also a handful of AirBnB's and VRBO's nearby.</li>

    </ul>
  </div>

    <!-- Get Involved Section -->
    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Want to be involved in Undermine 2026?</h2>
      <p class="mt-4">
        Are you interested in being a part of the next Heatpunk Summit? Have questions? Hardware you want to bring? Want to join our hashrate heating collaboration group? Reach out below.
      </p>
      <div class="flex justify-center mt-12 mb-12">
